title: Software Development Services Agreement
summary: SaaS platform build — enterprise CRM module
meta: | type: contract | ref: SA-2026-089 | theme: legal | date: 2026-06-24

section: 1. Definitions
def: Services | meaning: Design, development, testing, and deployment of the CRM module described in Schedule A
def: Deliverables | meaning: Source code, documentation, and deployment artifacts
def: Confidential Information | meaning: All non-public technical, commercial, and operational data disclosed by either party

section: 2. Parties
contact: NexaSoft Technologies W.L.L. | role: Provider | email: legal@nexasoft.qa | vat: VAT-301122
contact: Al-Majd Retail Group W.L.L. | role: Client | email: procurement@almajd.qa | vat: VAT-302233

section: 3. Scope of Services
text: Provider shall deliver the CRM module including: lead management, opportunity tracking, automated workflows, and reporting dashboard.

section: 4. Clauses
clause: Indemnity | scope: Provider | cap: 6 months fees | excludes: indirect damages, consequential loss
clause: Limitation of Liability | cap: 500,000 QAR | excludes: gross negligence, willful misconduct
clause: Force Majeure | meaning: Events beyond a party's reasonable control including acts of government, war, natural disaster

section: 5. Obligations
obligation: Deliver Schedule A in full | owner: Provider | by: 2026-09-30
obligation: Provide access to staging environment | owner: Client | by: 2026-07-15
obligation: Conduct UAT and sign acceptance | owner: Client | by: 2026-10-15

section: 6. Warranties
warranty: Conforms to functional spec | owner: Provider | period: 90 days
warranty: Free of critical defects | owner: Provider | period: 12 months

section: 7. Service Level Agreement
sla: Response time | target: 2h | priority: P1 | period: 24/7
sla: Resolution time | target: 8h | priority: P1
sla: Uptime guarantee | target: 99.9% | period: monthly

section: 8. Intellectual Property
text: All pre-existing IP remains with its owner. Custom code developed under this agreement transfers to Client upon final payment.

section: 9. Confidentiality
text: Both parties agree to hold Confidential Information in strict confidence for a period of 5 years from disclosure.

section: 10. Governing Law
text: This agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Qatar and disputes shall be resolved by arbitration under the Qatar International Centre for Conciliation and Arbitration.

section: 11. Execution
route: sequential
require: legal
require: finance | when: value > 200000
require: managing_director
approve: Legal review complete | by: Omar Fakhroo | role: legal | at: 2026-06-20
approve: Finance clearance | by: Fatima Al-Sulaiti | role: finance | at: 2026-06-22
approve: Executed for NexaSoft | by: Khalid Al-Mansouri | role: managing_director | at: 2026-06-24